None      def __init__(self):         self.client = carla.client("localhost", 2000)         self.client.set_timeout(2.0)         self.world = self.client.get_world()         self.blueprint_library = self.world.get_blueprint_library()         self.bp = self.blueprint_library.filter('model3')[0]      def reset(self):         self.collision_hist = []         self.actor_list = []          self.transform = random.choice(self.world.get_map().get_spawn_points())         self.Vehicle = self.world.spawn_actor(self.bp, self.transform)         self.actor_list.append(self.Vehicle)          self.rgbcam = self.blueprint_library.find('sensor.camera.rgb')         self.rgbcam.set_attribute("img_size_x" f"{self.im_width}")         self.rgbcam.set_attribute("img_size_y" f"{self.im_height}")         self.rgbcam.set_attribute("fov", f"110")          transform = carla.Transform(carla.Location(x=2.5, z=0.7))         self.sensor = self.world.spawn_actor(self.rgbcam, transform, attach_to=self.Vehicle)         self.actor_list.append(self.sensor)         self.sensor.listen(lambda data: self.procces_img(data))          self.Vehicle.apply_control(throttle=0.0, brake=0.0)         time.sleep(7)          colsensor = self.blueprint_library.find('sensor.other.collision')         self.colsensor = self.world.spawn_actor(colsensor, transform, attach_to=self.Vehicle)         self.actor_list.append(colsensor)         self.colsensor.listen(lambda event: self.collision_data(event))         while self.front_cam     def collision_data(self, event):         self.collision_hist.append(event)       def procces_img(self, image):         i = np.array(image.raw_data)         i2 = i.reshape((self.im_height, self.im_width, 4))         i3 = i2[:, :, :3]         if self.show_cam:             cv2.imshow("", i3)             cv2.waitKey(1)         self.front_cam = i3       def step(self, action):         if action == 0:             self.Vehicle.apply_control(carla.VehicleControl(throttle=1.0, steer=-1*self.steer_amt))         if action == 1:             self.Vehicle.apply_control(carla.VehicleControl(throttle=1.0, steer=0))         elif action == 2:             self.Vehicle.apply_control(carla.VehicleControl(throttle=1.0, steer=1 * self.steer_amt))         v = self.Vehicle.get_velocity()         kmh = int(3.6 * math.sqrt(v.x**2 + v.y**2 + v.z**2))          if len(self.collision_hist) != 0:             done = True             reward = -200         elif kmh<55:             done = False             reward = -1         else:             done = False             reward = 1         if self.gen_start + 50 < time.time():             done = True          return self.front_cam, reward, done, None class DQNAgent:     def __init__(self):         self.model = self.create_model()         self.target_model = self.create_model()         self.target_model.set_weights(self.model.get_weights())          self.replay_memory = deque(maxlen=car_env.REPLAY_MEMORY_SIZE)         self.tensorboard = ModifiedTensorBoard(Log_dir=f"logs/{MODEL_NAME}-{int(time.time())}")         self.target_update_counter = 0         self.graph = tf.get_default_graph()          self.TERMINATE = False         self.lastloggedgen = 0         self.trainintialized = False     def create_model(self):         base_model = Xception(wieghts=None, include_top=False, input_shape(IM_HEIGHT, IM_WIDTH, 3))         x = base_model.output         x = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)          predictions = Dense(3, activation="linear")(x)         model = Model(inputs=base_model.input, outputs=predictions)         model.compile(Loss="mse", optimizer=Adam(Lr=0.001), metrics=["accuracy"])         return model     def updatereplaymemory(self, transition):         self.replay_memory.append(transition)     def train(self):         if len(self.replay_memory) < car_env.MIN_REPLAY_MEMORY_SIZE:             return         minibatch = random.sample(self.replay_memory, car_env.MINIBATCH_SIZE)         current_states = np.array([transition[0] for transition in minibatch])/255         with self.graph.as_default():             current_qs_list = self.model.predict(current_states, car_env.PREDECTIONBATCHSIZE)         new_current_states = np.array([transition[3] for transition in minibatch]) / 255         with self.graph.as_default():             future_qs_list = self.target_model.predict(new_current_states, car_env.PREDECTIONBATCHSIZE)          x = []         y = []          for index, (current_state, action, reward, new_state, done) in enumerate(minibatch):             if not done:                 max_future_q = np.max(future_qs_list[index])                 new_q = reward + car_env.DISCOUNT * max_future_q             else:                 new_q = reward              current_qs = current_qs_list[index]             current_qs[action] = new_q              x.append(current_state)             y.append(current_qs)          logstep = False         if self.tensorboard.step > self.lastloggedgen:             logstep = True             self.lastloggen = self.tensorboard.step          with self.graph.as_default():             self.model.fit(np.array(x)/255, np.array(y), batch_size=car_env.TRAININGBATCHSIZE, verbose=0, shuffle=False, callbacks=[self.tensorboard] if logstep else None)          if logstep:             self.target_update_counter += 1          if self.target_update_counter > car_env.UPDATETARGETEVERY:             self.target_model.set_weights(self.model.get_weights())             self.target_update_counter = 0      def getqs(self, state):             return self.model.predict(np.array(state).reshape(-1 *state.shape)/255)[0]      def train_in_loop(self):         X = np.random.uniform(size=(1, 480, 640, 3)).astype(np.float32)         y = np.random.uniform(size=(1,3)).astype(np.float)         with self.graph.as_default():             self.model.fit(X,y, verbose=False, batch_size=1)         self.trainintialized = True          while True:             if self.TERMINATE:                 return             self.train()             time.sleep(0.01)

author: @BigBadBurrow
text: Here's a function I wrote to calculate required decay rate.  You can set start epsilon, and the epsilon value you want to have reduced down to after specified number of episodes.  def calculateDecay(initial_epsilon, final_decay_value, decay_rate, decay_rate_reducer, step_target, total_steps):          decay_value = initial_epsilon     previous_decay_rate = decay_rate      while True:         for this_step in range(total_steps):             decay_value *= decay_rate             if decay_value < final_decay_value:                 if this_step <= step_target and decay_rate_reducer <= 0.0_000_001:                     return decay_rate                 elif this_step > step_target:                     break                 else:                     return calculateDecay(initial_epsilon, final_decay_value, previous_decay_rate, (decay_rate_reducer*0.1), step_target, total_steps)              if this_step > step_target:                 break          # decay faster         previous_decay_rate = decay_rate         decay_rate -= decay_rate_reducer         decay_value = initial_epsilon   if __name__ == '__main__':          initial_epsilon = 1 # initial epsilon     final_decay_value = 0.01 # epsilon value wanted at step_target     decay_final_reached = 0.75 # reach the final_decay_value at 0.75 of the number of steps     total_steps = 100000     decay_rate = 0.99999999999     decay_rate_reducer = 0.1      step_target = math.ceil( total_steps * decay_final_reached )      print( calculateDecay(initial_epsilon, final_decay_value, decay_rate, decay_rate_reducer, step_target, total_steps) )

author: @MrDanikong
text: 9:40 Not sure if I am right there how the decay behaves, but you could do something like that to calc the number of episodes or decay  MIN_EPSILON = START_EPSILON * EPSILON_DECAY^EPISODES    -->  EPSILON_DECAY = (MIN_EPSILON / START_EPSILON)^(1 / EPISODES) -->  EPISODES = log(MIN_EPSILON / START_EPSILON)/log(EPSILON_DECAY)
